{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729349609,"sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wfMk9lJTIMptPTVpdacHwJV1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py","offset":130,"limit":55},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n130: - Specific enough to trigger in similar situations\n131: - General enough to apply beyond this exact case\n132: - Actionable — the agent should know what to DO differently\n133: \n134: Respond with JSON:\n135: {{\n136:   \"condition\": \"IF/WHEN this situation arises (describe the trigger condition)\",\n137:   \"action\": \"THEN do this instead (describe the corrective action)\",\n138:   \"confidence\": 0.0 to 1.0 (how confident are you this rule is correct and useful),\n139:   \"reasoning\": \"brief explanation of why this rule would help\"\n140: }}\n141: \"\"\"\n142: \n143: \n144: # -- Weight adjustment --------------------------------------------------------\n145: \n146: \n147: _ADJUST_WEIGHTS_BULK_SQL = text(\n148:     \"\"\"\n149:     WITH old_vals AS (\n150:         SELECT id, weight AS old_weight\n151:           FROM memories\n152:          WHERE id IN :mids\n153:            AND tenant_id = :tid\n154:            AND deleted_at IS NULL\n155:     )\n156:     UPDATE memories\n157:        SET weight = GREATEST(:floor, LEAST(:cap, weight + :delta))\n158:       FROM old_vals\n159:      WHERE memories.id = old_vals.id\n160:        AND memories.tenant_id = :tid\n161:        AND memories.deleted_at IS NULL\n162:     RETURNING memories.id AS id, old_vals.old_weight AS old_weight,\n163:               memories.weight AS new_weight\n164:     \"\"\"\n165: ).bindparams(bindparam(\"mids\", expanding=True))\n166: \n167: \n168: # Backfill the rule memory's metadata.source_outcome_id after the outcome\n169: # exists. Rule persistence happens before outcome persistence (so the outcome\n170: # can record the rule_memory_id), so at rule-write time the outcome_id is\n171: # unknown. This UPDATE completes the rule→outcome traceability link.\n172: _BACKFILL_RULE_OUTCOME_SQL = text(\n173:     \"\"\"\n174:     UPDATE memories\n175:        SET metadata = jsonb_set(\n176:            COALESCE(metadata, '{}'::jsonb),\n177:            '{source_outcome_id}',\n178:            to_jsonb(CAST(:outcome_id AS text))\n179:        )\n180:      WHERE id = :rule_id AND tenant_id = :tid\n181:     \"\"\"\n182: )\n183: \n184: \n\n(Showing lines 130-184 of 1007. Use offset=185 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- Specific enough to trigger in similar situations\n- General enough to apply beyond this exact case\n- Actionable — the agent should know what to DO differently\n\nRespond with JSON:\n{{\n  \"condition\": \"IF/WHEN this situation arises (describe the trigger condition)\",\n  \"action\": \"THEN do this instead (describe the corrective action)\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.0 to 1.0 (how confident are you this rule is correct and useful),\n  \"reasoning\": \"brief explanation of why this rule would help\"\n}}\n\"\"\"\n\n\n# -- Weight adjustment --------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n_ADJUST_WEIGHTS_BULK_SQL = text(\n    \"\"\"\n    WITH old_vals AS (","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py","text":"- Specific enough to trigger in similar situations\n- General enough to apply beyond this exact case\n- Actionable — the agent should know what to DO differently\n\nRespond with JSON:\n{{\n  \"condition\": \"IF/WHEN this situation arises (describe the trigger condition)\",\n  \"action\": \"THEN do this instead (describe the corrective action)\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.0 to 1.0 (how confident are you this rule is correct and useful),\n  \"reasoning\": \"brief explanation of why this rule would help\"\n}}\n\"\"\"\n\n\n# -- Weight adjustment --------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n_ADJUST_WEIGHTS_BULK_SQL = text(\n    \"\"\"\n    WITH old_vals AS (\n        SELECT id, weight AS old_weight\n          FROM memories\n         WHERE id IN :mids\n           AND tenant_id = :tid\n           AND deleted_at IS NULL\n    )\n    UPDATE memories\n       SET weight = GREATEST(:floor, LEAST(:cap, weight + :delta))\n      FROM old_vals\n     WHERE memories.id = old_vals.id\n       AND memories.tenant_id = :tid\n       AND memories.deleted_at IS NULL\n    RETURNING memories.id AS id, old_vals.old_weight AS old_weight,\n              memories.weight AS new_weight\n    \"\"\"\n).bindparams(bindparam(\"mids\", expanding=True))\n\n\n# Backfill the rule memory's metadata.source_outcome_id after the outcome\n# exists. Rule persistence happens before outcome persistence (so the outcome\n# can record the rule_memory_id), so at rule-write time the outcome_id is\n# unknown. This UPDATE completes the rule→outcome traceability link.\n_BACKFILL_RULE_OUTCOME_SQL = text(\n    \"\"\"\n    UPDATE memories\n       SET metadata = jsonb_set(\n           COALESCE(metadata, '{}'::jsonb),\n           '{source_outcome_id}',\n           to_jsonb(CAST(:outcome_id AS text))\n       )\n     WHERE id = :rule_id AND tenant_id = :tid\n    \"\"\"\n)\n\n","lineStart":130,"lineEnd":184,"totalLines":1007,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py","time":{"start":1780729349597,"end":1780729349607}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d56e8502e3526a5016a23c60589f88191ba5b1b4d00fde3b3"}},"id":"prt_e9bbd85ba0018JVDO6bc9Mwofd","sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","messageID":"msg_e9bbd5082001fI33UNC94fv8jX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729349609,"sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9ItBqZUoxyuA6cUPOUrb1dh7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py","offset":540,"limit":85},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n540:             \"condition\": str(raw.get(\"condition\", \"\"))[:500],\n541:             \"action\": str(raw.get(\"action\", \"\"))[:500],\n542:             \"confidence\": confidence,\n543:             \"reasoning\": str(raw.get(\"reasoning\", \"\"))[:500],\n544:         },\n545:     )\n546: \n547: \n548: # -- Persist ------------------------------------------------------------------\n549: \n550: \n551: async def _persist_outcome(\n552:     db: AsyncSession,\n553:     tenant_id: str,\n554:     agent_id: str,\n555:     fleet_id: str | None,\n556:     outcome: str,\n557:     outcome_type: str,\n558:     related_ids: list[str],\n559:     weight_adjustments: list[dict],\n560:     rule_memory_id: str | None,\n561:     scope: str,\n562: ) -> str:\n563:     \"\"\"Write the outcome as a memory of type 'outcome'. Returns outcome memory ID.\n564: \n565:     `rule_memory_id` is the ID of the rule memory persisted in Phase 4 (or None\n566:     if no rule met the confidence threshold). Storing the resolved ID — rather\n567:     than a `rule_generated` boolean — avoids the case where the flag claims a\n568:     rule exists but no corresponding memory was actually created.\n569: \n570:     `scope` determines the outcome memory's visibility via _SCOPE_TO_VISIBILITY\n571:     so scope='agent' outcomes stay private and scope='all' outcomes are visible\n572:     tenant-wide.\n573:     \"\"\"\n574:     from core_api.schemas import MemoryCreate\n575:     from core_api.services.memory_service import create_memory\n576: \n577:     # Failure outcomes get higher weight — more informative for future analysis\n578:     weight_map = {\"success\": 0.6, \"failure\": 0.7, \"partial\": 0.5}\n579: \n580:     # Cap outcome length to bound persisted content size (consistent with\n581:     # rule fields capped at 500 chars in _generate_rule).\n582:     content = f\"[Outcome/{outcome_type}] {outcome[:2000]}\"\n583: \n584:     data = MemoryCreate(\n585:         tenant_id=tenant_id,\n586:         agent_id=agent_id,\n587:         fleet_id=fleet_id,\n588:         memory_type=\"outcome\",\n589:         content=content,\n590:         weight=weight_map.get(outcome_type, 0.5),\n591:         metadata={\n592:             \"outcome_type\": outcome_type,\n593:             \"related_memory_ids\": related_ids,\n594:             \"weight_adjustments\": weight_adjustments,\n595:             \"rule_memory_id\": rule_memory_id,\n596:             \"scope\": scope,\n597:         },\n598:         visibility=_SCOPE_TO_VISIBILITY.get(scope, \"scope_team\"),\n599:         write_mode=\"fast\",\n600:     )\n601: \n602:     # Savepoint isolates a DB error inside create_memory so the outer\n603:     # transaction stays usable. Outcome persistence is mandatory (unlike\n604:     # the rule), so re-raise after the savepoint rolls back to signal\n605:     # failure to the caller.\n606:     try:\n607:         async with db.begin_nested():\n608:             result = await create_memory(db, data)\n609:     except Exception:\n610:         logger.exception(\"evolve: failed to persist outcome\")\n611:         raise\n612:     return str(result.id)\n613: \n614: \n615: async def _persist_rule(\n616:     db: AsyncSession,\n617:     tenant_id: str,\n618:     agent_id: str,\n619:     fleet_id: str | None,\n620:     rule: dict,\n621:     scope: str,\n622:     outcome_id: str | None = None,\n623: ) -> str | None:\n624:     \"\"\"Write a generated rule as a memory of type 'rule'. Returns rule memory ID.\n\n(Showing lines 540-624 of 1007. Use offset=625 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"            \"condition\": str(raw.get(\"condition\", \"\"))[:500],\n            \"action\": str(raw.get(\"action\", \"\"))[:500],\n            \"confidence\": confidence,\n            \"reasoning\": str(raw.get(\"reasoning\", \"\"))[:500],\n        },\n    )\n\n\n# -- Persist ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\nasync def _persist_outcome(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    agent_id: str,\n    fleet_id: str | None,\n    outcome: str,\n    outcome_type: str,\n    related_ids: list[str],\n    weight_adjustments: list[dict],","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py","text":"            \"condition\": str(raw.get(\"condition\", \"\"))[:500],\n            \"action\": str(raw.get(\"action\", \"\"))[:500],\n            \"confidence\": confidence,\n            \"reasoning\": str(raw.get(\"reasoning\", \"\"))[:500],\n        },\n    )\n\n\n# -- Persist ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\nasync def _persist_outcome(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    agent_id: str,\n    fleet_id: str | None,\n    outcome: str,\n    outcome_type: str,\n    related_ids: list[str],\n    weight_adjustments: list[dict],\n    rule_memory_id: str | None,\n    scope: str,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Write the outcome as a memory of type 'outcome'. Returns outcome memory ID.\n\n    `rule_memory_id` is the ID of the rule memory persisted in Phase 4 (or None\n    if no rule met the confidence threshold). Storing the resolved ID — rather\n    than a `rule_generated` boolean — avoids the case where the flag claims a\n    rule exists but no corresponding memory was actually created.\n\n    `scope` determines the outcome memory's visibility via _SCOPE_TO_VISIBILITY\n    so scope='agent' outcomes stay private and scope='all' outcomes are visible\n    tenant-wide.\n    \"\"\"\n    from core_api.schemas import MemoryCreate\n    from core_api.services.memory_service import create_memory\n\n    # Failure outcomes get higher weight — more informative for future analysis\n    weight_map = {\"success\": 0.6, \"failure\": 0.7, \"partial\": 0.5}\n\n    # Cap outcome length to bound persisted content size (consistent with\n    # rule fields capped at 500 chars in _generate_rule).\n    content = f\"[Outcome/{outcome_type}] {outcome[:2000]}\"\n\n    data = MemoryCreate(\n        tenant_id=tenant_id,\n        agent_id=agent_id,\n        fleet_id=fleet_id,\n        memory_type=\"outcome\",\n        content=content,\n        weight=weight_map.get(outcome_type, 0.5),\n        metadata={\n            \"outcome_type\": outcome_type,\n            \"related_memory_ids\": related_ids,\n            \"weight_adjustments\": weight_adjustments,\n            \"rule_memory_id\": rule_memory_id,\n            \"scope\": scope,\n        },\n        visibility=_SCOPE_TO_VISIBILITY.get(scope, \"scope_team\"),\n        write_mode=\"fast\",\n    )\n\n    # Savepoint isolates a DB error inside create_memory so the outer\n    # transaction stays usable. Outcome persistence is mandatory (unlike\n    # the rule), so re-raise after the savepoint rolls back to signal\n    # failure to the caller.\n    try:\n        async with db.begin_nested():\n            result = await create_memory(db, data)\n    except Exception:\n        logger.exception(\"evolve: failed to persist outcome\")\n        raise\n    return str(result.id)\n\n\nasync def _persist_rule(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    agent_id: str,\n    fleet_id: str | None,\n    rule: dict,\n    scope: str,\n    outcome_id: str | None = None,\n) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Write a generated rule as a memory of type 'rule'. Returns rule memory ID.","lineStart":540,"lineEnd":624,"totalLines":1007,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/evolve_service.py","time":{"start":1780729349600,"end":1780729349608}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d56e8502e3526a5016a23c6058a0c8191a94c9bd87e89749f"}},"id":"prt_e9bbd85de001KyuVadsL5QkmMJ","sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","messageID":"msg_e9bbd5082001fI33UNC94fv8jX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729349642,"sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Q9TdPEO0UdO8OptbpxzXGyr1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py","offset":900,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n900:             else_=0.0,\n901:         ).label(\"vec_sim\")\n902:         has_embedding = Memory.embedding.is_not(None).label(\"has_embedding\")\n903: \n904:         ts_query = func.plainto_tsquery(\"english\", query)\n905:         raw_fts = func.ts_rank_cd(Memory.search_vector, ts_query)\n906:         fts_score = (raw_fts / (1.0 + raw_fts)).label(\"fts_score\")\n907: \n908:         # CAURA-679: NULL-embedding rows fall back to `fts_score` alone\n909:         # rather than the `(1 - w) * 0 + w * fts_score` haircut that\n910:         # the unconditional blend would apply. The haircut multiplies\n911:         # the FTS signal by `fts_weight` (≤1), so an FTS-matching but\n912:         # unembedded row could rank below noise-floor-cosine embedded\n913:         # rows (vec_sim ~0.15-0.20 from high-dim sphere clustering),\n914:         # which then drop it past the `LIMIT top_k * overfetch_factor`\n915:         # cutoff. This protects the FTS-fallback contract for both the\n916:         # CAURA-594 deferred-embed window and any case where the embed\n917:         # worker fails permanently — the row stays discoverable rather\n918:         # than silently undiscoverable.\n919:         similarity = case(\n920:             (\n921:                 Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n922:                 (1.0 - _fts_weight) * vec_sim + _fts_weight * fts_score,\n923:             ),\n924:             else_=fts_score,\n925:         ).label(\"similarity\")\n926: \n927:         anchor = func.greatest(\n928:             Memory.created_at,\n929:             func.coalesce(Memory.ts_valid_start, Memory.created_at),\n930:         )\n931:         age_days = func.extract(\"epoch\", func.now() - anchor) / 86400.0\n932: \n933:         type_decay = case(\n934:             *[(Memory.memory_type == mt, float(days)) for mt, days in TYPE_DECAY_DAYS.items()],\n935:             else_=float(_freshness_decay_days),\n936:         ).label(\"type_decay_days\")\n937: \n938:         freshness = case(\n939:             (\n940:                 and_(\n941:                     Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None),\n942:                     Memory.ts_valid_end < func.now(),\n943:                 ),\n944:                 _freshness_floor,\n945:             ),\n946:             (Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None), 1.0),\n947:             (\n948:                 age_days < type_decay,\n949:                 1.0 - (age_days / type_decay) * (1.0 - _freshness_floor),\n950:             ),\n951:             else_=_freshness_floor,\n952:         ).label(\"freshness\")\n953: \n954:         if recall_boost_enabled:\n955:             days_since_recall = (\n956:                 func.extract(\n957:                     \"epoch\",\n958:                     func.now() - func.coalesce(Memory.last_recalled_at, Memory.created_at),\n959:                 )\n960:                 / 86400.0\n961:             )\n962:             recency_factor = func.greatest(0.0, 1.0 - days_since_recall / _recall_decay_window_days)\n963:             recall_boost_expr = (\n964:                 1.0\n965:                 + (_recall_boost_cap - 1.0)\n966:                 * recency_factor\n967:                 * Memory.recall_count\n968:                 / (Memory.recall_count + RECALL_BOOST_SCALE)\n969:             ).label(\"recall_boost\")\n970:         else:\n971:             recall_boost_expr = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"recall_boost\")\n972: \n973:         base_score = (_similarity_blend * similarity + (1.0 - _similarity_blend) * Memory.weight).label(\n974:             \"base_score\"\n975:         )\n976: \n977:         if temporal_window is not None:\n978:             cutoff = func.now() - temporal_window\n979:             temporal_boost = case(\n980:                 (Memory.created_at >= cutoff, 1.3),\n981:                 else_=1.0,\n982:             ).label(\"temporal_boost\")\n983:         else:\n984:             temporal_boost = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"temporal_boost\")\n985: \n986:         # Soft date-range boost: multiplies the score for memories whose\n987:         # anchor date falls inside the query-extracted window.  Pairs with\n988:         # tighter padding in ``_extract_temporal_date_range`` — replaces\n989:         # the old hard WHERE filter so semantically strong out-of-range\n\n(Showing lines 900-989 of 4754. Use offset=990 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"            else_=0.0,\n        ).label(\"vec_sim\")\n        has_embedding = Memory.embedding.is_not(None).label(\"has_embedding\")\n\n        ts_query = func.plainto_tsquery(\"english\", query)\n        raw_fts = func.ts_rank_cd(Memory.search_vector, ts_query)\n        fts_score = (raw_fts / (1.0 + raw_fts)).label(\"fts_score\")\n\n        # CAURA-679: NULL-embedding rows fall back to `fts_score` alone\n        # rather than the `(1 - w) * 0 + w * fts_score` haircut that\n        # the unconditional blend would apply. The haircut multiplies\n        # the FTS signal by `fts_weight` (≤1), so an FTS-matching but\n        # unembedded row could rank below noise-floor-cosine embedded\n        # rows (vec_sim ~0.15-0.20 from high-dim sphere clustering),\n        # which then drop it past the `LIMIT top_k * overfetch_factor`\n        # cutoff. This protects the FTS-fallback contract for both the\n        # CAURA-594 deferred-embed window and any case where the embed\n        # worker fails permanently — the row stays discoverable rather\n        # than silently undiscoverable.\n        similarity = case(","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py","text":"            else_=0.0,\n        ).label(\"vec_sim\")\n        has_embedding = Memory.embedding.is_not(None).label(\"has_embedding\")\n\n        ts_query = func.plainto_tsquery(\"english\", query)\n        raw_fts = func.ts_rank_cd(Memory.search_vector, ts_query)\n        fts_score = (raw_fts / (1.0 + raw_fts)).label(\"fts_score\")\n\n        # CAURA-679: NULL-embedding rows fall back to `fts_score` alone\n        # rather than the `(1 - w) * 0 + w * fts_score` haircut that\n        # the unconditional blend would apply. The haircut multiplies\n        # the FTS signal by `fts_weight` (≤1), so an FTS-matching but\n        # unembedded row could rank below noise-floor-cosine embedded\n        # rows (vec_sim ~0.15-0.20 from high-dim sphere clustering),\n        # which then drop it past the `LIMIT top_k * overfetch_factor`\n        # cutoff. This protects the FTS-fallback contract for both the\n        # CAURA-594 deferred-embed window and any case where the embed\n        # worker fails permanently — the row stays discoverable rather\n        # than silently undiscoverable.\n        similarity = case(\n            (\n                Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n                (1.0 - _fts_weight) * vec_sim + _fts_weight * fts_score,\n            ),\n            else_=fts_score,\n        ).label(\"similarity\")\n\n        anchor = func.greatest(\n            Memory.created_at,\n            func.coalesce(Memory.ts_valid_start, Memory.created_at),\n        )\n        age_days = func.extract(\"epoch\", func.now() - anchor) / 86400.0\n\n        type_decay = case(\n            *[(Memory.memory_type == mt, float(days)) for mt, days in TYPE_DECAY_DAYS.items()],\n            else_=float(_freshness_decay_days),\n        ).label(\"type_decay_days\")\n\n        freshness = case(\n            (\n                and_(\n                    Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None),\n                    Memory.ts_valid_end < func.now(),\n                ),\n                _freshness_floor,\n            ),\n            (Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None), 1.0),\n            (\n                age_days < type_decay,\n                1.0 - (age_days / type_decay) * (1.0 - _freshness_floor),\n            ),\n            else_=_freshness_floor,\n        ).label(\"freshness\")\n\n        if recall_boost_enabled:\n            days_since_recall = (\n                func.extract(\n                    \"epoch\",\n                    func.now() - func.coalesce(Memory.last_recalled_at, Memory.created_at),\n                )\n                / 86400.0\n            )\n            recency_factor = func.greatest(0.0, 1.0 - days_since_recall / _recall_decay_window_days)\n            recall_boost_expr = (\n                1.0\n                + (_recall_boost_cap - 1.0)\n                * recency_factor\n                * Memory.recall_count\n                / (Memory.recall_count + RECALL_BOOST_SCALE)\n            ).label(\"recall_boost\")\n        else:\n            recall_boost_expr = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"recall_boost\")\n\n        base_score = (_similarity_blend * similarity + (1.0 - _similarity_blend) * Memory.weight).label(\n            \"base_score\"\n        )\n\n        if temporal_window is not None:\n            cutoff = func.now() - temporal_window\n            temporal_boost = case(\n                (Memory.created_at >= cutoff, 1.3),\n                else_=1.0,\n            ).label(\"temporal_boost\")\n        else:\n            temporal_boost = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"temporal_boost\")\n\n        # Soft date-range boost: multiplies the score for memories whose\n        # anchor date falls inside the query-extracted window.  Pairs with\n        # tighter padding in ``_extract_temporal_date_range`` — replaces\n        # the old hard WHERE filter so semantically strong out-of-range","lineStart":900,"lineEnd":989,"totalLines":4754,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py","time":{"start":1780729349634,"end":1780729349641}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d56e8502e3526a5016a23c6058a1481918a1fb1f1418e469a"}},"id":"prt_e9bbd85e1001SvALfTA2mIpI3b","sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","messageID":"msg_e9bbd5082001fI33UNC94fv8jX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729349659,"sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qqNS0Kbe19Y4jXy8iVNY1G32","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/enrichment/constants.py","offset":90,"limit":35},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/enrichment/constants.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n90:         \"(durable knowledge) instead, and let memclaw_insights \"\n91:         \"crystallise patterns over your corpus.\"\n92:     ),\n93: }\n94: \n95: MEMORY_TYPES = tuple(t.value for t in MemoryType)\n96: \n97: # C3/C8 — Memory types the SERVER generates internally and that agents\n98: # MUST NOT supply explicitly on the write boundary. ``outcome`` and\n99: # ``rule`` come out of evolve_service; ``insight`` comes out of\n100: # insights_service. Each is still a valid value at the storage layer\n101: # (the schema enum is unchanged) — only the route + MCP boundaries\n102: # reject explicit agent-supplied values.\n103: #\n104: # CAURA-699 — the LLM auto-classifier must NOT mint these from agent\n105: # content either: the enrichment prompt omits them from the offered\n106: # vocabulary (see ``common.enrichment._prompts``) and ``_validate_enrichment``\n107: # demotes any reserved type that slips through to ``DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE``.\n108: # The reserved types only ever reach storage via the internal flows above,\n109: # which set ``memory_type`` explicitly and bypass the classifier path.\n110: SERVER_RESERVED_MEMORY_TYPES: frozenset[str] = frozenset({\"outcome\", \"rule\", \"insight\"})\n111: \n112: # Import-time guard: enum and description dict must agree, otherwise\n113: # the prompt renderer will silently emit a bullet without a heading or\n114: # a heading without a description. Catching here gives a loud import\n115: # error rather than mysterious LLM behaviour.\n116: assert set(MEMORY_TYPES) == set(MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS.keys()), (\n117:     \"MemoryType enum and MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS keys are out of sync: \"\n118:     f\"enum-only={set(MEMORY_TYPES) - set(MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS)}, \"\n119:     f\"dict-only={set(MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS) - set(MEMORY_TYPES)}\"\n120: )\n121: \n122: # C3/C8 — every reserved type must exist in the enum / description set;\n123: # otherwise the boundary check below is referencing a phantom slug.\n124: assert SERVER_RESERVED_MEMORY_TYPES.issubset(set(MEMORY_TYPES)), (\n\n(Showing lines 90-124 of 148. Use offset=125 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        \"(durable knowledge) instead, and let memclaw_insights \"\n        \"crystallise patterns over your corpus.\"\n    ),\n}\n\nMEMORY_TYPES = tuple(t.value for t in MemoryType)\n\n# C3/C8 — Memory types the SERVER generates internally and that agents\n# MUST NOT supply explicitly on the write boundary. ``outcome`` and\n# ``rule`` come out of evolve_service; ``insight`` comes out of\n# insights_service. Each is still a valid value at the storage layer\n# (the schema enum is unchanged) — only the route + MCP boundaries\n# reject explicit agent-supplied values.\n#\n# CAURA-699 — the LLM auto-classifier must NOT mint these from agent\n# content either: the enrichment prompt omits them from the offered\n# vocabulary (see ``common.enrichment._prompts``) and ``_validate_enrichment``\n# demotes any reserved type that slips through to ``DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE``.\n# The reserved types only ever reach storage via the internal flows above,\n# which set ``memory_type`` explicitly and bypass the classifier path.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/enrichment/constants.py","text":"        \"(durable knowledge) instead, and let memclaw_insights \"\n        \"crystallise patterns over your corpus.\"\n    ),\n}\n\nMEMORY_TYPES = tuple(t.value for t in MemoryType)\n\n# C3/C8 — Memory types the SERVER generates internally and that agents\n# MUST NOT supply explicitly on the write boundary. ``outcome`` and\n# ``rule`` come out of evolve_service; ``insight`` comes out of\n# insights_service. Each is still a valid value at the storage layer\n# (the schema enum is unchanged) — only the route + MCP boundaries\n# reject explicit agent-supplied values.\n#\n# CAURA-699 — the LLM auto-classifier must NOT mint these from agent\n# content either: the enrichment prompt omits them from the offered\n# vocabulary (see ``common.enrichment._prompts``) and ``_validate_enrichment``\n# demotes any reserved type that slips through to ``DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE``.\n# The reserved types only ever reach storage via the internal flows above,\n# which set ``memory_type`` explicitly and bypass the classifier path.\nSERVER_RESERVED_MEMORY_TYPES: frozenset[str] = frozenset({\"outcome\", \"rule\", \"insight\"})\n\n# Import-time guard: enum and description dict must agree, otherwise\n# the prompt renderer will silently emit a bullet without a heading or\n# a heading without a description. Catching here gives a loud import\n# error rather than mysterious LLM behaviour.\nassert set(MEMORY_TYPES) == set(MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS.keys()), (\n    \"MemoryType enum and MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS keys are out of sync: \"\n    f\"enum-only={set(MEMORY_TYPES) - set(MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS)}, \"\n    f\"dict-only={set(MEMORY_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS) - set(MEMORY_TYPES)}\"\n)\n\n# C3/C8 — every reserved type must exist in the enum / description set;\n# otherwise the boundary check below is referencing a phantom slug.\nassert SERVER_RESERVED_MEMORY_TYPES.issubset(set(MEMORY_TYPES)), (","lineStart":90,"lineEnd":124,"totalLines":148,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/enrichment/constants.py","time":{"start":1780729349653,"end":1780729349659}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d56e8502e3526a5016a23c6058a1c819181c30e9f34c855f0"}},"id":"prt_e9bbd8610001CkMd9qZzrB0jcy","sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","messageID":"msg_e9bbd5082001fI33UNC94fv8jX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729349662,"sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4E22jYMqEZc5lpRWCLXjvjDI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py","offset":90,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n90:     soft_delete_memory,\n91:     update_memory,\n92: )\n93: from core_api.services.tenants import list_active_tenant_ids\n94: from core_api.services.usage_service import bulk_check_and_increment, check_and_increment\n95: \n96: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n97: \n98: router = APIRouter(tags=[\"Memory\"])\n99: \n100: \n101: def _reject_reserved_memory_type(memory_type: str | None, *, index: int | None = None) -> None:\n102:     \"\"\"C3/C8 — reject agent-supplied reserved memory types at the API boundary.\n103: \n104:     Reserved types (``outcome``, ``rule``, ``insight``) are emitted by the\n105:     server's internal write paths — evolve_service for outcome/rule,\n106:     insights_service for insight. Agents writing them explicitly creates\n107:     rows that downstream queries treat as system-authored, polluting\n108:     insights / RL signals. Internal callers go through\n109:     ``services.memory_service.create_memory`` directly and bypass this\n110:     check; only the REST + MCP entry points are gated.\n111: \n112:     ``index`` names the offending row in a bulk request so the operator\n113:     can find it; absent on the single-write path.\n114:     \"\"\"\n115:     if memory_type is None or memory_type not in SERVER_RESERVED_MEMORY_TYPES:\n116:         return\n117:     # ``memory_type`` is a ``MemoryType`` str-Enum value; ``!r`` would render\n118:     # ``<MemoryType.INSIGHT: 'insight'>`` which leaks the wrapper into the\n119:     # operator-facing message. ``.value`` (when present) gives the raw slug\n120:     # the API actually accepts; plain ``str(...)`` is the fallback.\n121:     slug = memory_type.value if hasattr(memory_type, \"value\") else str(memory_type)\n122:     detail = (\n123:         f\"memory_type='{slug}' is server-reserved and cannot be \"\n124:         \"supplied on writes. Use memclaw_evolve for outcome/rule or \"\n125:         \"memclaw_insights for insight; for agent-authored reflections, \"\n126:         \"use memory_type='semantic' or 'fact' (or omit memory_type to \"\n127:         \"auto-classify).\"\n128:     )\n129:     if index is not None:\n130:         detail = f\"items[{index}]: {detail}\"\n131:     raise HTTPException(status_code=422, detail=detail)\n132: \n133: \n134: async def _stats_fallback(tenant_id: str, fleet_id: str | None) -> dict:\n135:     \"\"\"Map storage-api's ``memory_compute_health_stats`` shape onto the\n136:     flat ``{total, by_type, by_agent, by_status}`` shape both stats\n137:     endpoints return. ``by_agent`` is empty because storage-api doesn't\n138:     compute it; ``partial: True`` flags the degradation so callers can\n139:     distinguish a real empty tenant from a degraded response.\n\n(Showing lines 90-139 of 2023. Use offset=140 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    soft_delete_memory,\n    update_memory,\n)\nfrom core_api.services.tenants import list_active_tenant_ids\nfrom core_api.services.usage_service import bulk_check_and_increment, check_and_increment\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nrouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"Memory\"])\n\n\ndef _reject_reserved_memory_type(memory_type: str | None, *, index: int | None = None) -> None:\n    \"\"\"C3/C8 — reject agent-supplied reserved memory types at the API boundary.\n\n    Reserved types (``outcome``, ``rule``, ``insight``) are emitted by the\n    server's internal write paths — evolve_service for outcome/rule,\n    insights_service for insight. Agents writing them explicitly creates\n    rows that downstream queries treat as system-authored, polluting\n    insights / RL signals. Internal callers go through\n    ``services.memory_service.create_memory`` directly and bypass this","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py","text":"    soft_delete_memory,\n    update_memory,\n)\nfrom core_api.services.tenants import list_active_tenant_ids\nfrom core_api.services.usage_service import bulk_check_and_increment, check_and_increment\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nrouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"Memory\"])\n\n\ndef _reject_reserved_memory_type(memory_type: str | None, *, index: int | None = None) -> None:\n    \"\"\"C3/C8 — reject agent-supplied reserved memory types at the API boundary.\n\n    Reserved types (``outcome``, ``rule``, ``insight``) are emitted by the\n    server's internal write paths — evolve_service for outcome/rule,\n    insights_service for insight. Agents writing them explicitly creates\n    rows that downstream queries treat as system-authored, polluting\n    insights / RL signals. Internal callers go through\n    ``services.memory_service.create_memory`` directly and bypass this\n    check; only the REST + MCP entry points are gated.\n\n    ``index`` names the offending row in a bulk request so the operator\n    can find it; absent on the single-write path.\n    \"\"\"\n    if memory_type is None or memory_type not in SERVER_RESERVED_MEMORY_TYPES:\n        return\n    # ``memory_type`` is a ``MemoryType`` str-Enum value; ``!r`` would render\n    # ``<MemoryType.INSIGHT: 'insight'>`` which leaks the wrapper into the\n    # operator-facing message. ``.value`` (when present) gives the raw slug\n    # the API actually accepts; plain ``str(...)`` is the fallback.\n    slug = memory_type.value if hasattr(memory_type, \"value\") else str(memory_type)\n    detail = (\n        f\"memory_type='{slug}' is server-reserved and cannot be \"\n        \"supplied on writes. Use memclaw_evolve for outcome/rule or \"\n        \"memclaw_insights for insight; for agent-authored reflections, \"\n        \"use memory_type='semantic' or 'fact' (or omit memory_type to \"\n        \"auto-classify).\"\n    )\n    if index is not None:\n        detail = f\"items[{index}]: {detail}\"\n    raise HTTPException(status_code=422, detail=detail)\n\n\nasync def _stats_fallback(tenant_id: str, fleet_id: str | None) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Map storage-api's ``memory_compute_health_stats`` shape onto the\n    flat ``{total, by_type, by_agent, by_status}`` shape both stats\n    endpoints return. ``by_agent`` is empty because storage-api doesn't\n    compute it; ``partial: True`` flags the degradation so callers can\n    distinguish a real empty tenant from a degraded response.","lineStart":90,"lineEnd":139,"totalLines":2023,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/memories.py","time":{"start":1780729349655,"end":1780729349662}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d56e8502e3526a5016a23c6058a2881919299bc535871057c"}},"id":"prt_e9bbd8616001EQeYfejqbn1V2g","sessionID":"ses_16443656effeEz6GoJAQaGGpUT","messageID":"msg_e9bbd5082001fI33UNC94fv8jX"}}
